Twitter on Friday flagged a post by US President Donald Trump on the unrest in Minneapolis as ‘glorifying violence’, saying the tweet violated its rules but would not be removed. “This Tweet violated the Twitter Rules about glorifying violence. However, Twitter has determined that it may be in the public’s interest for the Tweet to remain accessible,” the social media giant said. <img class="size-medium wp-image-1400494 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?resize=300%2C153&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="300" height="153" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?resize=300%2C153&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?resize=58%2C30&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?resize=260%2C133&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?resize=200%2C102&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Trump.jpg?w=532&amp;ssl=1 532w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> More details later… Vanguard News Nigeria. Twitter said Thursday it would label and deprioritize tweets from politicians that break its rules -- in a move that could affect the prodigious output of US President Donald Trump. June 27, 2019 In "News" Apple on Monday deleted most of the podcasts of the far-right conspiracy theorist Alex Jones, while Facebook removed four of his online pages which the social media platform accused of "glorifying violence." August 6, 2018 In "News" Twitter said it began enforcing new rules Monday aimed at filtering out "hateful" and "abusive" content on the social network including messages which promote or glorify violence. December 18, 2017 In "News"